race.comment: THE LIONS' GATE (7) was in good order before being outclassed in that $100k race at Ascot last time out. His form prior was very good, particularly over the short course at Northam two back. Can lob just off the speed and land the knockout blow. ROYAL ACCOLADE (2) bolted in over this course and distance 8 days ago, putting up an impressive 3.2L victory. Tougher here, but he's open to further improvement third-up and the claim of Nottle comes in handy. Loves this track and trip and can bring up back-to-back wins. TROPICAL SUN (6) is knocking on the door of another victory, finishing 1.6L off the winner last time out at Bunbury. She'll be back from the wide draw, but she's racing in top order and looks a leading contender. BUSTER'S GIRL (11) has been impressive in her two runs for the McCallum yard and can continue her strong form. PENNED (9) hasn't been far away in recent performances and can be in the finish once again.
